<item>
            <title>[OAK-3167] [Blob GC] Wrong time units for blobGcMaxAge are passed from SegmentNodeStoreService</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-3167</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;MarkSweepGarbageCollector#maxLastModifiedInterval expects time in millis while SegmentNodeStoreService passes the parameter in seconds. Due to this any blobs created after marking references and may be garbage collected.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This can lead to lucene index corruption if async indexing run happened simultaneously with garbage collection. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
